{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17524277","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17524277"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:03:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:03:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13981"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13981","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13981"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.35,0.06,0.28,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6615"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"88732"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6615","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6615"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2024-07-19T20:45:41+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-05T20:19:13+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2024-07-28T23:39:19+09:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-29 11:53:50"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13981"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72942"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"45"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1367"},{"type":"tags","id":"4862"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"13385"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13386"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35470"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72942"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"88732","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/88732"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 54-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for follow-up. She has quadriplegia following a motor vehicle accident two years ago. She reports developing a sore over her left hip in the past week. Her medical history includes C4 complete spinal cord injury. She takes baclofen for spasticity. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. A lesion over the left greater trochanter is noted (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Order magnetic resonance imaging of the hip","Perform surgical debridement","Prescribe oral antibiotics","Assess pressure-relieving strategies","Apply hydrocolloid dressing"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with a stage II/III pressure ulcer over a bony prominence, which is a common complication in patients with spinal cord injury due to immobility and sensory loss. The ulcer is relatively shallow, with a collection of necrotic tissue. The most important initial step is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eassess pressure-relieving strategies\u003C/strong\u003E to address the underlying cause and prevent further tissue damage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMagnetic resonance imaging of the hip\u003C/strong\u003E would be indicated if there were concerns about deep tissue involvement, osteomyelitis, or underlying collection. However, this is a superficial ulcer without signs of deep tissue involvement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESurgical debridement\u003C/strong\u003E is not appropriate for a clean stage II pressure ulcer. Debridement is reserved for wounds with significant necrotic tissue or non-viable tissue that requires removal. The necrotic tissue in this ulcer is superficial and easily removed with wound cleansing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrescribing oral antibiotics\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated as there are no clinical signs of infection such as surrounding erythema, warmth, or purulent discharge. Antibiotics should only be prescribed when there is clinical evidence of infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EApplying hydrocolloid dressing\u003C/strong\u003E may be appropriate as part of the management plan, but addressing the underlying cause through pressure relief takes priority. The choice of dressing should be based on wound characteristics and exudate levels.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA comprehensive pressure ulcer management plan should include regular repositioning, appropriate support surfaces, nutritional assessment, moisture management, and patient education. The goal is to remove pressure from the affected area and create optimal conditions for wound healing while preventing further skin breakdown.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pressure ulcer prevention requires comprehensive assessment of contributing factors including mobility, nutrition, and skin care.","Stage II pressure ulcers present with partial thickness skin loss and exposed dermis.","The priority in pressure ulcer management is addressing the underlying cause through pressure relief and repositioning."],"references":["Rosin NR, Tabibi RS, Trimbath JD, Henzel MK. A Primary Care Provider\u0027s Guide to Prevention and Management of Pressure Injury and Skin Breakdown in People With Spinal Cord Injury. Top Spinal Cord Inj Rehabil. 2020;26(3):177-185. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33192045/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72942"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13981"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20874"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20874","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20874"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/uQDsJ5A9PLhYGHRZgZ5shNRQoKCGEm.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/uQDsJ5A9PLhYGHRZgZ5shNRQoKCGEm.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1125}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72942","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/72942"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-06T19:34:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-06T19:36:03+10:30","number":11,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2025-03-06T19:35:27+10:30","plagiarismScore":0,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-6615-11.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250929%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250929T053310Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=c24becbe42c2b97fabe5b0f68a9bd58735a53ab9a1f4fdf6ae100af0ce825570"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6615"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"88732"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"45","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/45"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83e\uddbd","name":"Rehabilitation Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64